					We say that a hypergraph Γ=(V,H) is connected if, for every pair of vertices v,w∈ V, there exists a path that connects v and w, i.e. there exist v_1,…,v_m∈ V and h_1,…,h_m-1∈ H such that:


  * v_1=v;

  * v_m=w;

  * {v_i,v_i+1}⊆ h_i for each i=1,…,m-1.

				We say that Γ=(V,H) has k connected components if there exist Γ_1=(V_1,H_1),…,Γ_k=(V_k,H_k) such that:


  * For every i∈{1,…,k}, Γ_i is a connected hypergraph with V_i⊆ V and H_i⊆ H;

  * For every i,j∈{1,…,k}, i≠ j, V_i∩ V_j=∅ and therefore also H_i∩ H_j=∅.

