A lattice polytope 𝒫 is ℓ-reflexive if, for some ℓ∈_>0, the following conditions hold:


  * 𝒫 contains the origin in its (strict) interior;

  * The vertices of 𝒫 are primitive;

  * For any facet F of 𝒫 the local index ℓ_F = ℓ.

A lattice polytope P is called l-reflexive if, for some l∈, the following conditions hold:


  * P contains the origin in its (strict) interior;

  * the vertices of P are primitive;

  * for any facet F of P the local index l_F equals l.

We also refer to P as a reflexive polytope of index l .

