Given a phylogenetic network N on X and a leaf x∈ X, the phylogenetic 
network N^_x is the result of deleting leaf x from N, together with its incident ♌edge, and applying the following ♌three operations until none is applicable:


  (i) suppress a degree-2 vertex;

  (ii) replace a pair of multi-edges by a single edge;

  (iii) collapse a ♌blob with precisely two incident cut-edges into a single vertex.

Given a phylogenetic network N on X and X'⊆ X, the phylogenetic X'-deck of N is the set {N^_x | x∈ X'}.

